bug.short_desc: Upload fails on choosing 'All Mobile Platforms' option for supported platforms

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 524233 screenshot
steps to reproduce: 1. Load https://addons.allizom.org/en-US/developers/addon/submit/2 2. Upload a mobile-only add-on 3. For supported platforms, select 'All Mobile platforms' 4. Click 'Continue'
expected behavior: * For a mobile-only add-on, desktop platform options are disabled after upload completes. * User moves on to the next step of add-on submission.
observed behavior: Upload fails with 'Select a valid choice. 9 is not one of the available choices.'
Upload fails with Select a valid choice. 9 is not one of the available choices
*** Bug 648308 has been marked as a duplicate of this bug. ***
this is a database issue; it looks like the migration script didn't run correctly maybe. I'm investigating.

For some reason the migration never ran but re-running it went fine and fixed the problem. I bumped the migration version here https://github.com/jbalogh/zamboni/commit/3aa02cfe10b02580aed7ca92071d17dcb17fbd13 and also cherry-picked to next. We should be good to go for 6.0.5

I'm able to upload an add-on with "All mobile platforms" selected.
Marking this as verified.
